Colombia Stock Movers: Canacol Energy Gains, Bancolombia Falls

-- B y   A n d r e a   J a r a m i l l o
-- 
2011-02-15T22:10:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-15/colombia-stock-movers-canacol-energy-gains-bancolombia-falls.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index slipped 0.3 percent to 14,498.10 while the
Colcap Index declined 0.6 percent to 1,692.43.    Canacol Energy Ltd . (CNEC CB), the Calgary-based oil
company that operates fields in South America, advanced 0.7
percent in 3,015 pesos. The  oil company ’s revenue more than
tripled in 2010 from the previous year driven by an increase in
production, it said in a statement yesterday.    Bancolombia SA  (BCOLO CB), the nation’s biggest lender,
declined 1 percent to 25,900 pesos. The bank yesterday announced
it won’t charge transaction fees for 60 percent of its clients.
While the move will generate losses initially, the lender’s goal
is to increase its client base, Interbolsa brokerage wrote in a
report to clients today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrea Jaramillo in Bogota at 
 ajaramillo1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
